morenci

Pulled out some of my best rough in ‘22 . If you got one of these you should be stoked . In +15yrs of collecting I’ve only had the opportunity to buy historic material like this 3 or 4 times. Each time I’ve cleared my bank account to get what is possible . Old rock I call it. I’ve always been drawn to the aesthetic of this mine, particularly the powder blues . Collectors refer to that as ‘middle to low grade’ in the hierarchy of collectibility from the mine . For me it is just fine, I don’t need stones to be $60 / carat to be electric⚡️ 
there’s not much of this material left in my collection, I’ve almost entirely stopped keeping stones for myself .. for the business I don’t adhere to a cut it all at once approach when processing the rock I have, instead, a lot of the rock I set aside for future times . 
well,
after +22yrs in corporate america I am now a full time turquoise trader which means.. those ‘future’ times are now. 
I only hope you get as much joy and inspiration from these as I do . never in my dreams did I think I would be able to distribute stones like these (pictured) I’m happy to do it w/ you all along for the ride . I don’t think it’s a mistake that we’re connected .

rather than cab this chunk of colina verde I cut up small chunks for inlay u can see in subsequent pics 👉🏽 

this one was claimed by ryan @conscious_creators who mined the material, the gifted to his mom 

what did you make this year that you’re proud of?

Sad to announce I had a USPS box full of turquoise cabs stolen from out front my place. I’m writing just in case y’all come across someone selling stones that look a lot like mine. Those include: Lavender, Damele, Blue Moon, Carico Lake, Lucin & more. 

There is always the possibility the box might show up. Otherwise the stones belong to the universe. Should you see them floating about (esp in Tucson this year) please let me know! There will be a reward. 

For future reference USPS is still following their covid protocol which allows the delivery guy to sign for a box and leave it. In this case they signed for my box and left it not in my lockbox but out front of my place. The box was insured for less than 10% of the value (not my decision) making this more or less a total loss. Be aware, ship with care!

• the closest guess at the time the giveaway is over wins everything pictured including free shipping. In the case of a tie, the winner will be chosen based on having guessed first chronologically. 💥 

That’s it! Winner will be announced on Sunday. Thanks for participating & good luck! ❤️

GIVE.A.WAY ~ Win these cabs for FREE by submitting your guesses below. As a way to say thanks and to kick off the summer I thought I’d offer this collection & the opportunity to win them as a small offering of gratitude. 

To win: the correct numerical answer is the total weight in grams subtracted from the total weight in carats of all the items in this picture. 

Simple rules are:
• each IG account can submit up to 15 guesses, ONE guess per comment.
• guesses can go past the decimal point to the hundredths ex: 700.07
• all guesses must be submitted by 5pm PST on Saturday, June 10th.
• if you win you must be willing to give away at least one of these cabs or something you make with them for free.
• feel free to share with your followers if you’d like.
• breath, smile & invest effort to be kind and empathetic.
• the closest guess at the time the giveaway is over wins everything pictured including free shipping. International winners must pay for shipping. 

In the case of a tie, the winner will be chosen based on having guessed first chronologically. 💥 

That’s it! Winner will be announced on Saturday. Thanks for participating & good luck! ❤️

new rock ~ natural San Pedro variscite . this was an 8lb chunk that got ground up with a cement saw getting cut in half (I asked for it to be cut at least once) I like the ribbon seams of color in the black host . it’s good hard rock dug up by hand by @crystaldig ✨ from here it gets slabbed (repeatedly) about 8-10mm thick . from the slab you can start to identify patterns for cutting cabochons . acknowledging that a lot of rock gets wasted in the process, a lot more than you’d imagine . fortunately this rock is good and hard so less likely to fracture which is a primary source of loss . I have already seen visions of jewelry I would like to make with it, split like earring pairs then combined back or wide inlayed across a cuff like the one I made with Ryan’s rock @conscious_creators where the pattern persists visually seamless from terminal to terminal . we shall see

I won’t have cabs for awhile , few months .. but eventually yes for you wonderful earth loving people

GIVE.A.WAY ~ Win these BISBEE cabs for FREE by submitting your guesses below. As a way to say thanks I’m offering this collection & the opportunity to win them as a small offering of gratitude. 

To win: the correct numerical answer is the total you get when you subtract the weight in grams from the total weight in carats of the items in this picture. 

These natural bisbee stones were cut by Bisbee legend (and friend) Bruce Mead before he passed. 

Simple rules are:
• each IG account can submit up to 15 guesses, ONE guess per comment.
• guesses can go past the decimal point to the hundredths ex: 700.07
• all guesses must be submitted by 5pm PST on Sunday, Aug 6th.
• if you win you must be willing to give away at least one of these cabs or something you make with them for free.
• feel free to share with your followers if you’d like.
• breath, smile & invest effort to be kind and empathetic.
• the closest guess at the time the giveaway is over wins everything pictured including free shipping. International winners must pay for shipping. 

In the case of a tie, the winner will be chosen based on having guessed first chronologically. 💥 

That’s it! Winner will be announced on Sunday.  Remember, be kind to your fellow humans, we need it now more than ever. Thanks for participating & good luck! ❤️
